name: Tater Tots® Nachos
author: SunnyDaysNora
summary: This delicious dish takes classic nachos and replaces the chips with Tater Tots®; they are absolutely addictive! Serve with your favorite nacho toppings!
ingredients: 1 (32 ounce) package frozen bite-size potato nuggets (such as Tater Tots®)
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C)
Arrange potato nuggets in a single layer on a baking sheet
Bake potato nuggets in the preheated oven until golden and heated through, 24 to 26 minutes
Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat
Cook and stir beef in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; drain and discard grease
Stir water and   mix into beef; cook and stir until liquid is thickened, 2 to 3 minutes
Pour cheese sauce into a microwave-safe bowl; heat in the microwave for 30 seconds, stir
Continue heating in 15-second intervals until hot, stirring between intervals
Spread potato nuggets on a serving plate
Top with meat, cheese sauce, sour cream, onion, and jalapeno slices
